Text: An Inbound Message For You Has Been Quarantinedhave received this message because someone has attempted to send you an email from outside of Enron with an attachment type that Enron does not allow into our messaging environment Your email has been quarantined and is being held at the MailSweeper server Sender Date Thu Jun Subject True Quote Login Information Attachment Type ScenariosIncomingInbound EXE Catcher A filename matching the file mask was detected tqtutorialexe ScenariosIncomingInbound DOC Catcher A filename matching the file mask was detected truequote users guide doc If the intended email is of valid businessrelated content and you believe it requires Enron resources to retrieve it you may call your Help Desk and ask to have it released from quarantine and delivered to your email Inbox Your message will be scanned and checked for viruses prior to requested release If it contains a virus or there is reason to suspect it is malicious code it will not be delivered North American Resolution Center European Resolution Center EES Help Desk ETS Solution Center Houston or Omaha Please DO NOT reply to this address as it is not a monitored system mailbox
